Chelsea Will Pay $49 Million for Neymar, Metro Says: Soccer Roundup

-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 
2011-06-13T09:14:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-13/chelsea-will-pay-49-million-for-neymar-metro-says-soccer-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the Web.  Neymar Move  Chelsea is ready to meet the 30 million pound ($48.7
million) asking-price for Brazilian striker Neymar,  Metro 
reported.  The London club has identified the 19-year-old as central
to its plans and is raising its offer after earlier failing to
bid high enough get an agreement with his team, Santos, last
year, Metro said.  Blues Action  Birmingham plans to take legal action if former coach Alex McLeish seeks to join Midlands rival  Aston Villa ,  the Sun 
reported.  McLeish announced he was quitting the Blues in a message
sent to the club by e-mail, according to the Sun.  Jones Deal  Manchester United will pay 20 million pounds for Phil Jones
after Blackburn rejected a 16-million pound offer, the  Daily
Mirror  reported.  Blackburn’s refusal came after the England Under-21 team
player had agreed to personal terms and passed a medical test at
United, the Mirror said.  Arsenal Spending  Arsenal owner Stan Kroenke is ready to pay nearly 110,000
pounds a week for winger Sami Nasri, who has balked at signing a
new contract,  the Daily Mail said .  Nasri’s contract expires at the end of next season, and the
Gunners were unwilling to meet his demands, offering 90,000
pounds a week, the newspaper said. Kroenke, who bought control
of the club this year, wants to keep the French national team
player, who has been linked with  Manchester United , the Mail
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Duff in  Madrid  at 
 aduff4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
